      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "# Recollect \u2014 RED service metrics\n(R)ate / (E)rrors / (D)uration for the command path, plus WS + match counters. All series come from the server's OTLP metrics (`recollect.commands.applied`, `recollect.command.duration_ms`, `recollect.ws.*`, `recollect.matches.*`) which arrive in Prometheus as `recollect_*_total` / `recollect_command_duration_ms_bucket`. A spike in the **reject ratio** is the cheap anti-cheat signal \u2014 honest clients never send illegal commands.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.3.3",
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
